        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 17 at 3:26PM EDT by NWS Albany NY</headline>
        <description>At 326 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Saratoga Springs, moving northeast at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Deans Corners, Grangerville, Northumberland, Wayville, Greenfield
Center, Middle Falls, Porter Corners, Halls Corner, Mannings Cove,
North Milton, Saratoga Race Course, Danielstown, Glens Falls, East
Hartford, South Corinth, Wilton, Dimmick Corners, Fortsville, Hudson
Falls, and Clarks Corner.

This includes Interstate 87 between exits 13S and 21.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 800 PM EDT for
east central New York...and southern Vermont.</instruction>
